      <body>
         <div>
            <pb facs="#facs_1" n="1" xml:id="img_0001"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_1_r1">
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l1" n="N001"/>
               <placeName ref="#place-7002482">Baghdad</placeName>
               <date when="1921-07-10"> July 10</date>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l2" n="N002"/> Darling <persName ref="#person-EH009">Mother</persName>. I've got your letter of <date when="1921-06-08">June 8</date>
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l3" n="N003"/>+ also the <seg type="bibliographicNote-target-text">Heart of Yorkshire<note type="bibliographic">
                     <bibl>
                        <author>Lady Florence Bell</author>, <title>The Heart of Yorkshire\u003a A Play in Three Parts and an Epilogue.</title>
                        <publisher>A. L. Humphreys: </publisher>
                        <date>1923</date>
                     </bibl>
                  </note>
               </seg> + I must write
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l4" n="N004"/>specially to tell you how charming I think 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l" n="N005"/> the play. It's full of poetry + grace - 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l7" n="N006"/> acted in its own setting it ought to have 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l8" n="N007"/> a tremendous effect. The sentiment of it 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l9" n="N008"/> is so delicious. How pretty the costumes
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l10" n="N009"/> will be, + the little modern scene will 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l11" n="N010"/> only emphasize them. But final allegory.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l12" n="N011"/> is the crown of it all - I <hi style="text-decoration: underline;">do</hi> think 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_l_478" n="N012"/> it's so good. Doesn't it seem a pity that 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l15" n="N013"/>I shan't see it.
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l16" n="N014"/> We're having an interesting time too, as you'll 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l17" n="N015"/>see in my letter to <persName ref="#person-EH006">Father</persName>. I'm sure we've 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l18" n="N016"/>done the right thing, but there have been 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l19" n="N017"/> moments of great anxiety + but for Sir
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l20" n="N018"/>
               <persName ref="#person-EH002">Percy</persName> we should never have succeeded. 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l21" n="N019"/> Once we've got <persName ref="#person-EH001">Faisal</persName> onto his throne which 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l22" n="N020"/> might almost be in the next fortnight, he'll 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l23" n="N021"/> gradually take charge himself, I hope. 
               <lb facs="#facs_1_r1l24" n="N022"/> But upon my soul he has got a difficult 
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_2" n="2" xml:id="img_0002"/>
            <ab facs="#facs_2_r1">
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l1" n="N001"/>task before <persName ref="#person-EH001">him</persName> + what amazes me is 
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l2" n="N002"/>that he should want to be King of Iraq.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l3" n="N003"/>However, it's a mercy that he does.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l4" n="N004"/> I need not say that I shall not go 
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l5" n="N005"/> to <placeName ref="#place-7000198">India</placeName> this summer. I'm very 
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l6" n="N006"/> well - I couldn't leave at this 
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l7" n="N007"/>juncture.
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l8" n="N008"/>Ever your very affectionate + 
               <lb facs="#facs_2_r1l9" n="N009"/> admiring daughter
               <lb facs="#facs_2_l" n="N010"/>Gertrude
            </ab>
            <pb facs="#facs_3" n="3" xml:id="img_0003"/>
